NOTE: The terms "hard bop" and "bebop" are subgenres of jazz music that emerged in the mid-20th century. Charlie Parker, Art Blakey, Cannonball Adderley, Horace Silver, and Clifford Brown were prominent musicians in the hard bop era. Blue Note Records was a record label known for its contributions to hard bop and jazz music. Jazz clubs were venues where hard bop and other forms of jazz music were performed.
